Date: 0/0/1913
Source: Country Work
Author: CARR
Vol / Page: 18
Edition:
Quote: A number of stations ... run a scour ... From five to seven men are generally employed ... at the wash, and the balance on the drying green. ... The work on the green [at the port scour] is practically the same as on a sheep station.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1913
Source: Country Work
Author: CARR
Vol / Page: 44
Edition:
Quote: [The flax fibre] is carted ... to the drying green, generally called the `paddock', where it is spread out to dry and bleach. ... It is [then] taken in hand by the `scutcher', who feeds it into a revolving drum ... which beats the refuse out.
